h2(#Introduction). Introduction

3dsMax MR Standard is a sIBL_GUI Template for 3dsMax and Mental Ray. It provides a bridge between 3dsMax, Mental Ray and Smart IBL. 
There is an Helper Script with everything you need to use sIBL_GUI smoothly with 3dsMax here : "sIBL_GUI For 3dsMax - Helper Script":http://www.hdrlabs.com/cgi-bin/forum/YaBB.pl?num=1223936394/2#2

h2(#Options). Options

h3. Common Attributes

* *Create Lights* : Create the sIBL Dynamics Lights.
* *Create Background* : Create the Background Environment Branch of the Raytype Shader ( Using the High Resolution LDR file of the current IBL Set ).
* *Create Reflection* : Create the Reflection Environment Branch of the Raytype Shader ( Using the Reflection HDR file of the current IBL Set ).
* *Create Lighting* : Create the Lighting Environment Branch of the Raytype Shader ( Using the Lighting HDR file of the current IBL Set ).
* *Create Sun* : Create the light used as Sun.

h3. Additional Attributes

* *Create Ground* : A Plane is added to the Scene.
* *Create FeedBack* : Create a viewport Visual Feedback with the current IBL LDR Background image.
* *Activate Linear Workflow* : Connect a Utility_Gamma___Gain__mi shader to the current Render Settings Lens Shader slot.
* *Feedback Radius* : Sets the Feedback radius in 3dsMax units.
* *Hide Lights* : Hides all current Scene lights.

